## Best Practices for Custom Services

### 1. Error Handling and Fallbacks

Always provide graceful fallbacks when platform features aren't available:

```csharp
public async Task<bool> TryPlatformFeatureAsync()
{
    try
    {
        // Try primary implementation
        return await PrimaryImplementation();
    }
    catch (PlatformNotSupportedException)
    {
        // Try fallback
        return await FallbackImplementation();
    }
    catch (Exception ex)
    {
        _logger.LogWarning(ex, "Platform feature unavailable");
        return false;
    }
}
```

### 2. Asynchronous Operations

Use async/await for operations that might block:

```csharp
public async Task<T> CallNativeServiceAsync<T>()
{
    return await Task.Run(() =>
    {
        // Long-running native operation
        return NativeInterop.PerformOperation();
    });
}
```

### 3. Resource Cleanup

Implement IDisposable for services that manage native resources:

```csharp
public class LinuxCustomService : ICustomPlatformService, IDisposable
{
    private DBusConnection _connection;
    private bool _disposed;

    public void Dispose()
    {
        Dispose(true);
        GC.SuppressFinalize(this);
    }

    protected virtual void Dispose(bool disposing)
    {
        if (!_disposed)
        {
            if (disposing)
            {
                _connection?.Dispose();
            }
            _disposed = true;
        }
    }
}
```

### 4. Thread Safety

Ensure thread-safe access to shared resources:

```csharp
private readonly SemaphoreSlim _semaphore = new SemaphoreSlim(1, 1);

public async Task<string> ThreadSafeOperationAsync()
{
    await _semaphore.WaitAsync();
    try
    {
        return await PerformOperation();
    }
    finally
    {
        _semaphore.Release();
    }
}
```

